🕵️‍♂️ Social Media Enumeration (SME)

Social Media Enumeration is the process of collecting information about a target from social platforms during passive reconnaissance (OSINT).

👉 Professionals use it to gather:
Emails & usernames
Personal details (job, location)
Company structure
Technologies used
Potential attack vectors (phishing, social engineering)
-------------------------------------

🔍 What Can You Find?

👤 Individual Targets
Full name, aliases
Email addresses
Phone numbers (sometimes exposed)
Photos (metadata clues)
Friends / connections

🏢 Company Targets
Employee list
Tech stack hints
Internal tools (from posts)
Office locations
Hiring patterns (very useful!)
-----------------------------------------

🌐 Top Platforms for Social Media Recon
LinkedIn → Employees, roles, org structure
Twitter → Real-time updates, opinions, leaks
Facebook → Personal data, relationships
Instagram → Images, locations, habits
GitHub → Developer emails, repos, secrets

---------------------------------------------

🛠️ Top Tools for Social Media Enumeration
🔹 1. Sherlock -> Finds usernames across 300+ platforms -> python3 sherlock username
🔹 2. Maigret -> Advanced alternative to Sherlock, Detects account existence + metadata
🔹 3. theHarvester -> Collects: Emails, Domains, Social profiles
🔹 4. Social-Analyzer -> Fast username enumeration, Supports many platforms
🔹 5. SpiderFoot -> Fully automated recon, Finds social accounts + leaks
🔹 6. Twint -> Scrapes tweets without API, Finds: Mentions, Hashtags, Emails
🔹 7. Holehe -> Checks where an email is registered, 👉 Great for account discovery
🔹 8. hunter.io -> extract emails from domain
🔹 9. namechk.com -> check username availability
